text: Location, location, location!! Cute house with recent updates just a block away from Grapevine's Main Street historical district! Enjoy the convenience of walking to all the nearby festivals, shops, restaurants, and wineries that downtown Grapevine has to offer. Nice sized back yard with huge shade tree to keep you nice and cool in the summer. All appliances including the refrigerator, washer and dryer are included. Recent updates include interior and exterior paint, lighting, with new tile and walk in showers in bathrooms. Come take a look, you won't be disappointed!

Fantastic corner-lot home in prime location just minutes from Grapevine Lake in a beautiful, tree-lined neighborhood! Major updates in the last 5 years include a new roof, HVAC, water heater, exterior siding and paint, most of the downstairs windows, stainless steel stove and microwave! Enjoy tons of amenities nearby, walking distance to the neighborhood park, Dove Waterpark, Playgrounds, Horseshoe Trail, and local sports complexes, plus all the shopping, dining, and entertainment that Grapevine has to offer. Step inside to a bright and inviting interior. The spacious layout flows from the main living room to the dining area, followed by the eat in kitchen and cozy family room. A convenient half bath downstairs is perfect for guests. Upstairs, youll find a large primary suite with double sinks, a soaking tub, separate shower, and a generous walk-in closet. Two additional bedrooms share a well-appointed hall bath. Out back, a large wood deck sets the stage for weekend BBQs and entertaining. The expansive yard offers plenty of space for pets, play, and outdoor fun, and includes a large storage shed for all your extras. Listed for a great price and won't last long, schedule your showing today!

text: Welcome to The Grapevine Brownstones Phase 2! This new construction Monticello plan presents a limited opportunity to own a luxury Lock and Leave Residence in the heart of Grapevine across from Hotel Vin, steps from Historic Main St, Peace Plaza, Harvest Hall and The Grapevine REC. A short walk across Dallas Rd to the TEX Rail which will drop you at DFW Airport or Ft. Worth and the The Grapevine Vintage RR with special excursion including the Stockyards and the Christmas Train. This beautiful Residence is 4 stories with 3 bdrm, 3.5 bath, 2 car garage and the 4th floor rooftop patio. Amenities include 12 foot ceilings in the kitchen and living room, luxurious showers, a unique 2nd floor balcony off the kitchen, and faces one of only two courtyards in the community. Enjoy easy access to many of the special events Grapevine offers including Main St Days, Grapefest, and all that comes with being The Christmas Capital of Texas. Walking is easy with a 75 Walkscore and also quick access to highways, Southlake Town Square, and DFW Airport. This home will be built elevator ready and the buyer can choose to add after closing.

Just one block from Grapevines Historic Main Street, the iconic Lipscomb House perfectly blends timeless 1888 charm with the modern luxuries of a full-scale renovation. Completely reimagined in 2017 with no expense spared, it features a helical pier foundation, foam encapsulation, double pane windows, and all-new systems. In 2024, it was further upgraded with fresh interior and exterior paint, a whole-house Culligan water filtration system, upscale light fixtures, and a fully floored attic above the oversized detached garage for excellent storage. The backyard was reimagined with the shed relocated and old planters removed to maximize green space. Inside, you'll find refinished hardwood floors, bold design selections, and high-end finishes throughout. The chefs kitchen is a true showpiece with a 48 6-burner Thermador gas range with double ovens, built-in Thermador refrigerator, pellet ice maker, drink fridge, and leathered quartzite countertops, all opening to the living and dining areas for effortless entertaining. Just off the main space is a warm and inviting library with rolling ladder and fireplace, a dedicated office, and a charming mudroom. The primary suite includes a luxurious walk-in closet that connects directly to a spacious laundry room with sink and built-ins. Upstairs, youll find two large bedrooms with en suite baths, a cozy reading loft, and built-in dressers for extra storage and charm. Situated on a corner lot with a large circular driveway, multiple patios, and a pool-ready backyard. Need more space? Architectural plans for a fourth bedroom are already drawn and available. Just minutes from parks, the Botanical Gardens, and all the best that Grapevine has to offerthis is a rare opportunity to own one of the citys most special homes.

text: Welcome to your future home, where luxury and comfort seamlessly combine. This stunning two-story residence, spanning 2, 823 square feet, is located in the highly sought-after neighborhood of Grapevine, TX, just moments from the serene beauty of Grapevine Lake. From the moment you approach the elegant double front doors, youll be captivated by the refined charm that awaits inside. Step into a grand foyer that leads to a spacious layout, offering four generously sized bedrooms and three beautifully appointed bathrooms, each featuring exquisite walk-in showers. The bathrooms are elegantly outfitted with marble countertops, exuding timeless beauty and sophistication. Every detail has been carefully curated with high-end finishes, including Delta fixtures and pristine white cabinetry. The heart of the home is the open-concept living area, where natural light pours in through the large windows and expansive 3-pane sliding door, leading to a sprawling back patio. Imagine relaxing evenings by the appliance fireplace, conveniently activated by a light switch, or adjusting the dimmable LED light switches to create the perfect mood for any occasion. The gourmet kitchen is a chefs dream, with gas appliances, sleek quartz countertops, and ample storage space. Whether youre preparing a family meal or entertaining guests, this kitchen will be the center of many cherished moments. This home also features a smart garage door and a roof with 30-year shingles, providing both modern convenience and lasting durability. With a 3-car garage and plenty of space for outdoor living, this home offers everything you need to live in luxury and style. Dont miss your chance to experience this exceptional home, located near the tranquility of Grapevine Lake, where sophistication meets comfort in the most perfect way.

text: Discover the perfect combination of luxury and functionality in this stunning 2, 239-square-foot residence located in Grapevine, TX, just moments from the picturesque Grapevine Lake. Pedestrian living at it's finest! This freshly updated Austin Stone 4 bedroom home features a luxurious and relaxing outdoor living space with a sterling waterfall pool and spa, cabana with sitting area, dining space and a very large grassy green lawn area. Located just a stone's throw away from Historic Downtown Grapevine which is lined with restaurants, galleries and shops makes these two worlds collide. Interiors showcase an open floor plan with views through the home, an updated and chic kitchen with stainless farm sink, ss appliances, white granite countertops and oversized subway tile backsplash and modernized ensuite primary bedroom. 4th bedroom can dual as a second living room or home office. See List of Updates from 2021. Highlights include: new roof, Lennox HVAC, replaced siding on the entire back wall of home, heavy Iron exterior doors, swimming pool with heated spa and Pentar Pool equipment, outdoor lighting. Conveniently located to Dallas Fort Worth International Airport, Downtown Grapevine, Highway 114 and a myriad of DFW's sports and entertainment arenas.

text: Discounted rate options and no lender fee future refinancing may be available for qualified buyers of this home. Beautifully updated single-story home located in the heart of Grapevine and zoned to highly acclaimed Grapevine Colleyville ISD. This 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom home features an open-concept layout with abundant natural light, luxury vinyl plank flooring throughout, and a modern kitchen with updated, stainless steel appliances, and a breakfast bar. The primary suite offers a walk-in custom closet and en-suite bathroom with updated lighting and large toilet. Enjoy a private, fully fenced backyard with privacy ideal for relaxing or entertaining. Just minutes from Historic Downtown Grapevine, Lake Grapevine, DFW Airport, and Southlake Town Square, with easy access to Hwy 121 and 114. This move-in ready home offers the perfect combination of location, updates, and charm.

Tucked at the end of a peaceful cul-de-sac, just a short walk from the shimmering shores of Lake Grapevine, stands a two-story home thats been loved, lived in, and carefully maintained since 1986. As you step through the front door, you're welcomed into a warm and inviting living room with soaring cathedral ceilings. A floor-to-ceiling brick fireplace anchors the space, enveloped by a wall of built-in bookcases. Overhead, a modern wagon wheel LED chandelier adds a touch of rustic elegance. The heart of the home is the kitchen, where morning coffee is shared at the eat-in nook and holiday meals are prepared for family and friends. Just beyond, theres a separate formal dining room, perfect for gatherings both big and small. Nearby, a spacious laundry room with extra storage and a convenient half bath make daily living easy. Upstairs, all three bedrooms are thoughtfully arranged for privacy and comfort. The primary suite offers its own en-suite bathroom, while two more bedrooms share a second full bath. Whether it's the laughter of children, the quiet hum of a home office, or the peace of a restful night's sleepthis upper level is ready for whatever life brings. Out back, a simple fenced yard and deck provide just enough space to enjoy the outdoorsno pool to maintain. Its the kind of yard where you can sip iced tea on a summer afternoon, grill on weekends, or let the dog run free. This all-electric home runs on city utilities, with upgraded security and fire alarm wiring in place (updated in early 2023). New carpet and luxury vinyl tile, installed in April 2023, Major items replaced since 2022 that include AC, Heat Pump, Hot Water Tank. Exterior professionally painted 4-24 with Sherwin Williams Paints and a 2019 Roof replacement add comfort and freshness throughout. So if you're looking for more than square footageif you're looking for a home with heart, history, and a future waiting to be writtenthis may be the one.

text: Dont miss this incredible 4-bedroom, 3-bathroom home on a cul-de-sac lot in an excellent Grapevine location just off 121, close to schools, shopping, dining, and DFW Airport. From the moment you arrive, youll love the beautifully manicured landscaping and curb appeal. Inside, the home has been freshly painted and features warm oak-colored luxury vinyl flooring throughout the main level, complete with extra padding for added comfort. The spacious living room includes a cozy direct-vent gas fireplace and flows into a large kitchen with double LG ovens, a gas cooktop, and plenty of room for cooking and entertaining. The dining room and breakfast nook sit on either side of the kitchen, with the nook offering views of the beautiful backyard. The oversized primary suite is tucked privately at the back of the home and includes space for a sitting area, a generous ensuite bath with dual vanities, and a walk-in closet. A second bedroom downstairswith a full bath just outsideis ideal for guests, kids, or multi-generational living. Upstairs, youll find two additional bedrooms, including one that can serve as a media room or office, plus a large game room with a walk-in closet and access to attic storage. Two separate walk-out attic spaces offer added convenience. text: Own a piece of Historic Downtown Grapevine! This five-unit apartment complex is within walking distance of Grapevines renowned restaurants, shops, wineries, and more. Welcome to a beautifully designed home that blends elegance with endless potential. This stunning 2, 576-square-foot residence, located in the coveted Grapevine, TX, offers the perfect balance of luxury and versatility. Currently a one-story home, it also offers the option to be transformed into a two-story masterpiece, allowing you to customize it to fit your unique vision. From the moment you step through the grand front door, youll be greeted by a space filled with natural light, thanks to an abundance of large windows throughout the home. The open floor plan features three spacious bedrooms and two and a half bathrooms, all adorned with premium finishes, including marble countertops in the bathrooms and sleek quartz countertops in the kitchen. Delta fixtures and LED dimmable light switches add a touch of modern elegance to every room. The heart of the home is the open-concept living area, where a 3-pane sliding back door seamlessly connects the indoors to the outdoor patio. Imagine enjoying serene evenings by the appliance fireplace, which is conveniently activated with the flip of a light switch, creating a cozy atmosphere thats perfect for relaxation. For the aspiring chef, the kitchen boasts gas appliances, ample storage, and a beautiful expanse of quartz countertops, making it a perfect space for preparing meals or entertaining guests. The pristine white cabinets create a timeless look that complements the homes sophisticated style. This home also offers a 3-car garage with a smart garage door opener, ensuring convenience and security. A 30-year shingle roof provides durability and peace of mind for years to come. Located near the tranquil beauty of Grapevine Lake, this home is the perfect setting to enjoy both luxurious living and natural surroundings. Dont miss the opportunity to make this exceptional home yours where luxury, comfort, and endless possibilities await.

Super low maintenance. Great neighbors!

text: Welcome to 4214 Hearthside situated in the highly sought-after Countryside Estates Addition in Grapevine zoned to highly acclaimed Grapevine-Colleyville ISD. As you walk into a raised entrance, you'll come to a living room that features high ceiling, one wall with 2 tall arched windows with a brick veneer fireplace in between and a separate dining room. The eat-in kitchen features a breakfast area, white crisp cabinets with a granite countertops, new stainless steel appliances dishwasher, single wall-oven, microwave and a drop-in smooth electric cooktop with a drop-down kitchen island range venthood that gives a sleek modern look. The kitchen flows into family room featuring one wall with filled windows offering plenty of natural light. The primary bedroom features high ceiling and an en-suite bathroom with a large white granite counter top vanity with double sinks, a unique cornered l-shape walk-in closet with double entrance. All bedrooms feature new carpet and vinyl wood looking flooring throughout the rest of the house. Backyard is fully fenced in. Don't miss out as there are not many homes available for sale in the prestigious Countryside Estates Addition. Easy access to HWY 121, close to Grapevine Lake, Downtown Grapevine, and more.

This beautifully updated 4-bedroom, 2.5-bath home in Hidden Lake Estates offers both comfort and lifestyle. Step inside to find pride of ownership throughout, with engineered hardwood flooring, crown molding, designer lighting, and custom stained cabinetry in the kitchen complemented by granite countertops, stainless steel appliances, double ovens, and a smooth-top cooktop. Updated windows fill the home with natural light, while wrought iron staircase spindles and a decorative mosaic tile fireplace add a touch of elegance. An electric gate provides privacy for the long driveway leading to the rear-entry garage. Out back, enjoy your own retreat with a covered patio, a large pool with three fountains, and a beautifully landscaped lot perfect for entertaining. For peace of mind, the home is equipped with a security system featuring cameras at the front and back doors, motion alarms, and fire, smoke, and glass break sensors. The community offers a private catch-and-release pond and park just a short walk away, with direct access next to the pond leading to the Grapevine Lake walking and biking trails, including the C. Shane Wilbanks Trail and Horseshoe Mountain Bike Trail. This home is the perfect blend of relaxation, security, and convenience near Grapevine Lake.

text: Willow Wood Horse Farm is without a doubt one of the finest examples of modern architecture combined with an equestrian lifestyle on 9.753+/- acres. The residence was originally designed by Lou Simmons, who collaborated with Bob Sullivan on the project to help it come into completion. Situated in the heart of the Dallas-Fort Worth Metroplex, just minutes from Lake Grapevine, Southlake, and an easy commute to DFW International Airport, this property affords someone the ability to have all the comforts of the city, while living just slightly removed from it all. The main residence and equestrian facilities are immaculate and ready for the next generation of ownership. This property is a must have for the individual desiring to be close to the city but enjoy a more peaceful and country-like setting. Improvements: This custom designed home was completed in 2022 and is truly an example of elegance. The 4, 353 SF home demands attention as it sits on the highest point of the property. Hear the rumble of your tires on the cobble stone drive as you approach the house and take in the modern architectural masterpiece that awaits. Situated on either side of the main door of the home is a beautifully understated Koi pond that welcomes visitors before entering through the massive glass door and entry way. The home is constructed of insulated concrete form (ICF) with steal joists and a deck roof system. Walls and windows of the home provide superior thermal and sound insulation. After walking through the threshold, you will notice a grand view all the way through the living areas of the house, overlooking the 3, 000 SF IPE back deck, 80 ft long salt water swimming pool, through the pasture to the equestrian facilities. The welcoming views are complimented by a very warm and luxurious open-concept living space that combines the living room, kitchen, and dining areas. Custom quarter sawn walnut millworker can be found throughout the kitchen and living areas as well as the rest of the residence. The kitchen is ideal for the master chef with Gagneau appliances including a steam convection oven, a conventional convection oven, coffee machine, cooktop, dishwasher, separate paneled refrigerator and freezer units, as well as a warming drawer. Just off the kitchen is a half bath and a full butlers pantry with prep space and a full-size dishwasher. Each of the bedrooms has a unique and different view of the property. The primary bedroom features similar views to the main living area, a spacious walk-in closet, a bathroom with solid stone bath tub and wash basins by Piet Boone, and Donrbracht platinum plumbing fixtures. The two additional bedrooms have on suite bathrooms also with Donrbracht fixtures and excellent clothing storage for family or guests. All main rooms have Italian pocket door hardware with soft open/close features and are fully sealed with gaskets to aid in sound transfer between rooms when doors are closed. Journeying up and down the custom-built metal framed staircase is an artistic treat in itself. Going up the stairs to the second floor viewing area re-emphasizes the stunning views of the grounds and surrounding area, complete with a dishwasher, fridge/freezer/icemaker, a dumbwaiter, and floor to ceiling windows and doors that open to a covered porch and roof top IPE deck. The lower level of the home features an acoustically balanced theater with Dynaudio speakers and sound system designed by Ember Audio to provide a true movie theater experience from the comfort of your own home. The theatre is complete with a 250-bottle wine cooler, 8 ft concert walls, and a powder bath. All of which could also be used as a very nice storm cellar.

text: WOW! Turn-Key! Look no further! Welcome to your meticulously cared for home, conveniently located in the middle of the Glade Crossing Subdivision, nestled among two independent tree-lined streets- Hazy Meadow Lane and Wonder Way! Homes on these two streets do not come up for sale very often! These two streets are unique in that they are not connected to any other streets within Glade Crossing, offering minimal traffic and quiet scenery. This home also has larger-than-typical space behind the lot adding to the privacy and quiet factor. NEW ROOF! Upon entry, you are greeted by a grand staircase featuring newly installed carpet and open-concept entryway. The lower level boasts bonus room that can be an office, living, or media room off the front of the home, or even an extra guest or grandparent bedroom! Eat-in kitchen features granite countertops, neutral-painted cabinets, newer appliances with induction cooktop, and a breakfast bar. Living room features soaring ceiling offering natural light through the grand large windows with wood shutters boasting views to the backyard, featuring custom landscaping and covered patio. Primary bedroom offers secluded privacy on lower-level opposite side of the home from the upstairs bedrooms, with remodeled primary bathroom featuring walk-in shower, double vanity, built-in custom tub, and large walk-in closet. Newly installed windows in most of the home!! Fresh neutral paint colors throughout every room! Newly installed carpet upstairs, with engineered hardwood and tile throughout the lower level. Zoned for Grapevine Elementary School, which is within short walking distance, as well as Colleyville Heritage Middle and High Schools! This centrally located home also offers easy walks to the dog park, trails, and other local recreational parks. This home has been very well maintained, and is truly move-in ready! Backyard is large enough for a pool, spa, kitchen and more! Check out docs for full feature list!

text: This modern home is in the sought after Grapevine-Colleyville ISD. The home was completely remodeled to have a modern appeal inside and out. Kitchen was completely remodeled with custom quartz counter tops with marble back splash and upgraded gas stove. Open concept for entertaining inside and large iron double doors open to a outside patio. The half-acre lot hosts one of the oldest trees on record in Grapevine. Landscaped and ready for pool or backyard oasis. Relax outside under the canopy covered porch or sit around a fire pit with modern down lighting. Beautiful Parr Park is less than .25 miles away. This special home boasts a new expanded primary luxury bedroom suite with his and her walk in closets, vaulted ceiling, and a spacious luxury bathroom with separate vanities, huge walk in shower and spa tub await you. A separate guest house for your guests, home office or a mother-in-law suite. House has an impressive custom-made pivot door with a full bath.

You cant beat this LOCATION! Nestled in the highly sought-after Yorkshire Meadows community, where homes rarely come on the market, this beautifully maintained single-story home offers a rare opportunity to own in a neighborhood that feeds into the exemplary Grapevine-Colleyville ISD and is within walking distance to all three top-rated schools. Step inside to discover a spacious layout featuring 3 bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, 2 living areas, a dedicated dining room, and a versatile flex space. Fresh carpet graces all bedrooms, while skylights and a double-sided gas fireplace between the living areas add warmth and charm. The kitchen is a chefs dream with granite countertops, stainless steel appliances, a window overlooking the side yard, and a wet bar ideal for entertaining. A convenient half bath is tucked off the back family roomperfect for guests. The primary suite is a true sanctuary with vaulted ceilings, fresh paint, new carpet, and its own private fireplace. Just off the primary, a bonus room offers the perfect space for a home office, gym, or nursery. Outside, the private backyard is a tranquil retreat with lush landscaping, adorable storage shed, and an electric gate offering both security and ample parking for Texas-sized vehicles or even an RV. The peaceful, one-way-in, one-way-out neighborhood includes a pocket park and fosters a serene, community feel. Major updates include a new roof (November 2024) and recently updated HVAC systems inside and out. The refrigerator, washer, and dryer will even convey with the home. Dont miss your chance to own in one of the most desirable pockets of Grapevine. This home checks all the boxes for comfort, convenience, and community. Book a showing at your own riskyou will fall in LOVE!

The perfect place for culinary enthusiasts. Rich red oak hardwoods grace the floors throughout with walls of windows allowing an abundance of natural light to stream through. The oversized Living leads to the Primary Bedroom overlooking the peaceful grounds. A beautifully updated ensuite bath boasts a walk in closet with custom closet system and remodeled shower. Two ample bedrooms complete the layout, both with walk in Closets. This home has been meticulously maintained. Full house piers to ensure stability, newer roofing, Windows replaced, and HVAC. PLUS Kitchenaid Gas Range and Dishwasher, Zline Microwave Drawer, Lighting Fixtures, Ceiling fans, Outdoor Wall lights, Bathroom Mirrors and More! A Large utility room with an abundance of cabinets and counter space. Adding more to the charm is the gorgeous lot and location. Enjoy the spacious grounds with room for a pool, greenhouse, or golf practice area. A huge redwood deck offers ample room for entertaining, dining or just relaxing listening to the birds. OR take off and enjoy an evening in Historic Grapevine at one of the many fun establishments. Whether dining, shopping or listening to live music. There is something for everyone! Fantastic access to Major Highways, DFW Airport, Grapevine Lake and Main Street Grapevine! A true must see for those looking for the charm of Grapevine in a thoughtfully maintained home.

text: Own a Piece of Grapevine History - The Iconic Blevins Farmhouse: A rare opportunity to own one of Grapevine's most treasured historic homes - the Blevins Farmhouse. This beautifully restored Queen Anne Victorian, originally built in 1903, has been thoughtfully updated to offer the perfect blend of vintage charm and modern convenience. A true landmark, the home was named for its original owners and generously donated to the City of Grapevine in 2017. It was carefully relocated from Continental Boulevard to the Historic Township, where its legacy continues to be preserved for future generations. Thoughtfully renovated between 2017 and 2020, the Blevins Farmhouse features an open-concept design with warm modern farmhouse finishes. Inside, you'll find light-filled living and kitchen spaces adorned with plantation shutters-ideal for entertaining. The owner's suite is a private retreat, complete with a cozy fireplace, soaking tub, dual showers, double vanity, and a spacious walk-in closet. No detail was overlooked in ensuring both beauty and functionality. Major systems-including foam insulation, windows, HVAC, plumbing, electrical, and even the foundation-were all updated and replaced, offering peace of mind and long-term energy efficiency. Located just two blocks from Historic Main Street, the home offers walkable access to Grapevine's vibrant shops, restaurants, wine-tasting rooms, and beloved community festivals. Whether you're drawn to architectural significance, historical charm, or a truly unique home with modern amenities, the Blevins Farmhouse is a one-of-a-kind gem ready for its next chapter.

text: Located just minutes to the boat launches at Grapevine Lake, this home can house your boat, toys, workshop, workout room, or the collection of cars of every hobbyist's dream! Check out the 4+ car barn with HVAC! With walkability to downtown Grapevine to the restaurants, shops, and wineries, you're sure to love this location! This historical home, known as the GE Hunt Home, was originally constructed in 1910 and rebuilt in 2016 through a meticulous renovation that preserved its soul while anchoring it in the now. Set on a lush half-acre lot filled with mature native trees, this home feels like a page out of Grapevines past with a future-proof foundation, literally built atop a modern steel pier-and-beam system. With over 4, 500 square feet under roof and 2, 780 square feet in the main home, the layout is as thoughtful as it is functional. Downstairs, the primary suite offers privacy and comfort with a spa-like ensuite bath, while a guest suite on the same floor provides hospitality with ease. A light-filled great room flows into the heart of the homea luxurious kitchen with Thermador appliances and era-inspired cabinetry and color, plus and a dining area designed for gathering. Upstairs, two additional bedrooms each feature full baths, accompanied by a second living area and an expansive office space that could double as a creative studio or library. The details tell the real story with preserved trimwork, hardwood floors, and antique-inspired fixtures which are all balanced by smart updates and energy-efficient systems. Outside, a 975 sq ft detached garage-workshop echoes the aesthetic of a classic Texas barn, offering functionality with curb appeal. And the porte-cochere near the mudroom and laundry isnt just a design feature, its a daily convenience, enhanced by the Generac generator, ready on demand to power the home. This is more than a historical homeits a legacy, lovingly restored and ready for its next chapter.

text: New construction!!! Welcome to The Grapevine Brownstones Phase 2! Worth and the The Grapevine Vintage RR with special excursions including the Stockyards and the Christmas Train. text: MARKET REFRESH We heard your feedback and made the improvements! Built by Centennial Homes, this light & bright 2-story has living areas downstairs, all sleeping rooms upstairs. text: Luxury, comfort, and impeccable design meet in this stunning custom home, ideally located near major highways and perched on one of Tarrant Countys highest elevations. Set on a heavily treed, shaded lot, this home offers a peaceful, park like setting perfect for relaxing outdoors or entertaining guests. Commuters will love the easy access to Highways 121, 114, and 360, making daily travel outside of this secluded neighborhood a breeze. The heart of the home is a large, centrally located kitchen featuring custom cabinets, granite countertops, and breakfast bar, plus tile backsplash, all connecting to the large breakfast nook and cozy family room. The main level owners retreat offers privacy and luxury with a fully renovated ensuite bath, with dual vanities, soaking tub, glass walk-in shower, and an oversized walk-in closet. Upstairs, a versatile loft provides the perfect space for a home office, reading nook, or media area, along with 3 generously sized bedrooms and a shared bath. Additional highlights include a rear entry garage with extra parking, a mudroom with enclosed storage, 2 water heaters, and 3 zoned HVAC units for year-round comfort. Dont miss your opportunity to own a move-in-ready home in a premier location schedule your viewing today! Sellers are offering a 2% concession to buyers with an acceptable offer
